This paper deals with natural language generation for the Semantic Web, which involves the use of computational linguistics and artificial intelligence techniques. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely categories. The paper also involves the use of RDF, OWL, and SPARQL, which are related to databases and information retrieval, making cs.DB (Databases) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) likely categories as well. Finally, the paper evaluates the framework's ability to generate natural language, which is related to machine learning and language modeling, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible category.
